name: Julia Thomason at Love the Mouse Travel
text: Beautiful horse barn stable venue for weddings and special events. Lots of options for the wedding ceremony and a great patio with stage, fireplace and string lights for a reception. Lots of photo opportunities! The owner was very friendly and gave us an informative tour.

text: I cannot say enough good things about Windwood Equestrian! The venue is absolutely gorgeous and made my wedding truly look like a dream. When you are venue shopping for your wedding, keep Windwood in mind!

text: This place is awesome..nice people and host. Will come back again,  highly recommended.   Trails are easy to challenging.   Beautiful..  my truck broke down 5 miles from town and everyone is such a big help getting it fixed.

name: Jennifer C Stanley
text: Friendly staff, clean restrooms, nice scenery, pull-through campsites.  Have to clean your stall before you can put your horse in it because other people leave them dirty and the staff doesn't check up on that.  Dogs are supposed to be on a leash, but people were letting them run loose in the campground and on trails.  A member of the staff said they "aren't worried about checking coggins papers."  Some campers came in late at night and put 2 horses per stall and there were awful fights and badly injured horses, but none of the staff seemed to care about enforcing rules.  The campground smelled like a sewer and all the trash cans in the campground were full the whole time we were there.  I recommend enjoying the trails on a day-use only basis.  Campsites are way too close together.
